31 Zoning ordinances and by-laws shall classify “accessory dwelling unit,” as defined
32 herein, as a use permitted by right in all single-family residential zoning districts. No zoning
33 ordinance or by-law shall unreasonably regulate the location, dimensions, or design of an
34 accessory dwelling unit on a lot. As used herein, “accessory dwelling unit” is a self-contained
35 housing unit incorporated within a single-family dwelling or detached accessory structure that is
36 clearly subordinate to the single-family dwelling and complies with the use, dimensional, and
37 design requirements of the local zoning ordinance or by-law.
